  "decision_conditions": [
    "There is no private amenity space provision for Flat 2, which is a three bedroom, four person unit and this would be harmful to the amenity of future occupiers as well as resulting in a worse quality provision of family accommodation than currently exists on site, contrary to Policies 7 and 9 of the Havering Local Plan, Policy D6 of the London Plan and the guidance in the National Planning Policy Framework.",
    "The proposed development would, by reason of insufficient car parking provision, result in increased parking congestion in surrounding streets contrary to Policy 24 of the Havering Local Plan and Policies T6 and T6.1 of the London Plan.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to Extension Plans UK via email on 12th February 2024."
